{
  "stem": "734.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 20.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But of course, mother knew about-- we-- I think my sister told mother exactly what happened one evening.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Mother said, that's my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] That's a, that's a, that's a story I'll, I'll remember it forever, probably, just to be there and to list-- to, just to watch her expressions when all this was happening, how she-- how sorry she felt for those two farmers, those poor people-- amazing.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gutman, yes--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he warned father about the fact that there is no future for Jews in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was as simple as that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- it became a very general issue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, everybody knew about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was not the only one who was aware of it, except that he was more aware than a lot of other people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was a very interesting man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I probably-- he, of all the people who would come into the house, stands out most in my mind, the most fascinating character.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a child-- well, seven, eight-- I used to listen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I used to love to listen to his stories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he would-- he would just have some amazingly interesting stories to tell.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was always a story to learn something from life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was always something that was absolutely fascinating, that was interesting that-- it made a lot of sense, you know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And mainly, he spoke about existence, and culture, and future, and the future of the Jews as a people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there is no future in this country-- that we must do everything possible to simply vacate this land, because it will never be good for us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we must think in terms of our own-- a roof over our own, over our own head.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
